Review_body:
There are many great aspects of this film - it's pretty, at times hilarious, with some great effects. There are also some terrible aspects of this film - great shots of New York City in the 1980's ruined with cheesy effects, awful music, terrible jokes and inconsistent directing. However, when you consider the pressure of being the sequel to 'Ghostbusters' (1984), as well as how many hands were involved in the process, then I guess this is a pretty good movie. Too many writers, being too good of friends with the director, having too long to mull over a 90 minute script (nearly 5 years) will always lead to a film that tries to do too much and lacks a clear tone.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
